European Coal Derivatives Gain 0.8%, First Advance in Four Days

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-04-14T10:16:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/european-coal-derivatives-gain-0-8-first-advance-in-four-days.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
rose for the first time in four days.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year gained $1, or 0.8 percent, to $130.25 a
metric ton by 11:06 a.m. in  London .  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  